! kind

Lightweight schema engine for TiddlyWiki. Define each type's fields, constraints, title formula, and namespace memberships on a single tiddler. Spawn, edit, view, and validate typed instances through hand-rolled UIs with zero plugin dependencies.

!! Key features

* ''One tiddler per type'' — schema lives in fields and a JSON-encoded `kind.fields` array on a single tiddler; body stays free for prose documentation
* ''Namespaces'' — types declare `kind.namespaces` (multi-membership); a namespace switcher scopes what's visible
* ''Auto-computed titles'' — types declare a `kind.title-formula` filter; new instances get their title computed from sibling fields
* ''Live + bulk validation'' — inline errors as you edit, plus a wiki-wide validator report
* ''Typeahead refs'' — filterable text input + dropdown + selected pills with × remove; scales to large option sets
* ''Configurable stream-river view'' — each type chooses which fields appear in its in-river field bar; empty = bar hidden
* ''Hand-rolled UI'' — zero dependency on other rimir plugins (theme/components/typed)

!! Prerequisites

No external prerequisites. Optional: `$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template` for the branded documentation hub.

!! Quick start

# Open the ''type-builder'' tab and define a new type (key, caption, icon, namespaces, title-formula, fields JSON).
# Open the ''creator'' tab, pick the type, fill the fields, click Create.
# Open the resulting tiddler in the story river — the stream-view field bar appears at the top.
# Use the ''validator'' tab for a wiki-wide constraint scan.
